<TEXT>
<P>
 Issues coming up 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 
</P>
<P>
 Planning Commission meeting 
</P>
<P>
 When: Today, 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Where: City Hall Council Chambers, 300 Centennial Way 
</P>
<P>
 What: Commission will consider a request by Fancher Development Services Inc. 
to open a fast-food restaurant with a drive-through lane at 14042 Red Hill Ave. 
Also on the agenda is a request by Red Robin International to establish a 
temporary parking area on a vacant portion of Tustin Market Place property. Red 
Robin restaurant is at 3015 El Camino Real. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 573-3000 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park 
</P>
<P>
 City Council study session 
</P>
<P>
 When: Today, 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Where: Civic Center Plaza, 6650 Beach Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 What: Council expected to give final approval to a revision of the 
comprehensive General Plan. Council gave preliminary approval to the plan over 
the objections of two school systems last week. The schools have said that they 
should get more revenue from a planned residential development on the site of 
the Lincoln Drive-In. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 562-3500 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 
</P>
<P>
 Unified School District and Neighborhood Committee meeting 
</P>
<P>
 When: Today, 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Where: First Presbyterian Church, 600 N. Main St. 
</P>
<P>
 What: Discussion about floor plans for a "space saver" intermediate school to 
be constructed at Bristol Marketplace. Space-saver schools typically have 
several stories, instead of taking up land with single-floor buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 558-5501 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 
</P>
<P>
 City Council meeting 
</P>
<P>
 When: Tuesday, 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Where: City Hall, 201 E. La Habra Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 What: Council will consider amending its anti-graffiti ordinance to crack down 
on vandals. The amendment may include imposing fines on those who break the 
law. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (310) 905-9700 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster 
</P>
<P>
 Joint meeting of City Council and Redevelopment Agency 
</P>
<P>
 When: Tuesday, 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Where: Council Chambers, 8200 Westminster Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 What: Joint study session on the proposed Community Cultural Center. 
Architects from the firm Anthony & Langsford will present new designs requested 
by council members. Also to be considered is a proposal to install more entry 
signs into the city. Signs have already been installed at the north and south 
entrance to the city on Beach Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 More Information: (714) 898-3311 
</P>
<P>
 This column is designed to provide a sampling of public meetings occurring 
this week in Orange County. For more information about meetings in your area, 
call your local government office. 
</P>
