<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: DRUNK-DRIVING ARRESTS DROP 40% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The number of drunk-driving arrests in Ventura County over the four-day 
holiday weekend dropped by more than 40% from a year ago, down to 19, the 
California Highway Patrol reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 "The word in general is getting out that drunk driving is just not acceptable 
anymore," a CHP spokesman said. "A lot more people are adhering to that, and 
they're either not drinking or they're designating a driver." 
</P>
<P>
 Over the four-day holiday last year, the CHP reported 33 drunk-driving 
arrests. 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP conducted a maximum enforcement period from Wednesday night to Sunday 
night, assigning all available officers to the area's streets and highways. 
JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
