<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For now, Orange County Ranger Ginny McVickar has the panoramic vistas and 
oak-filled canyons of Gen. Thomas F. Riley Wilderness Park largely to herself 
-- if you don't count the resident population of mule deer, coyotes, hawks and 
other wild creatures. 
</P>
<P>
 All that will change Dec. 10, when the 475-acre park opens its trail system to 
hikers, equestrians and mountain bikers. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of an opening day celebration, the park will offer free hay rides and 
guided tours. 
</P>
<P>
 The park, named after the retiring county supervisor, is at the east end of 
Oso Parkway, across from the Coto de Caza residential development near Mission 
Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 Today 
</P>
<P>
 The annual Holiday Craft Fair at Golden West College will begin in the student 
cafeteria. Hours of the boutique are 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raising event will feature holiday ornaments, jewelry, clothing, gift 
baskets and other handmade items. Some proceeds from the event will go to buy 
food and toys for needy families during the holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West College is at 15744 Golden West St., Huntington Beach.  
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 895-8261. 
</P>
</TEXT>
