<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; 4TH ROUND OF MEDFLY SPRAYING IS TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Weather permitting, the fourth aerial malathion spraying in eastern Camarillo 
will begin Tuesday to combat the Medfly infestation. 
</P>
<P>
 Three helicopters are scheduled to lift off from Camarillo Airport at 10 p.m. 
to begin the four-hour spraying of the mixture of the pesticide malathion and 
corn syrup. 
</P>
<P>
 Agriculture officials advise adults, children and their pets living inside the 
16-square-mile eradication zone to stay inside during the operation and make 
sure vehicles parked outside are covered. 
</P>
<P>
 The normal 9 p.m. takeoff time was pushed back one hour to accommodate 
nighttime holiday shoppers, officials said. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
