<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; 2 MEN SHOT AT PARTY; SUSPECT ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 39-year-old Santa Paula man is being held at Ventura County Jail on 
suspicion of recklessly discharging a firearm after two men were wounded at a 
weekend party, Santa Paula police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Pablo Navarette Acevedo at a house in the 100 block of Santa 
Ana Street about 8:15 p.m. Saturday after responding to a report of fighting 
and shots being fired at the residence, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two unidentified men were injured in the shooting, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that Acevedo started firing a gun during a fight at the 
party Saturday night, striking one man in the leg. Another man suffered a hand 
injury while attempting to disarm the suspect, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The condition of the men was not available Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Acevedo is being held on charges of discharging a firearm with gross 
negligence and willfully resisting arrest, a jail commander said Sunday. He is 
being held in lieu of $50,000 bail and is scheduled to be arraigned in Ventura 
County Municipal Court on Tuesday. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
