<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; 3 INTERCHANGE RAMPS AT KIMBALL REOPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five months after they were closed for renovations, three of the four 
interchange ramps on the Santa Paula Freeway at Kimball Road have reopened, 
Ventura city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The ramps were closed in June as part of a $10-million program to widen and 
make Kimball Road safer. 
</P>
<P>
 Both westbound on- and off-ramps, along with the eastbound off-ramp, are open, 
and the eastbound on-ramp is scheduled to open next week, Ventura Traffic 
Engineer Nazir Lalani said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, a bicycle and pedestrian underpass similar to the one at Victoria 
Avenue has been completed, Lalani said. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction on the Kimball widening project began in August, 1993, and will 
be completed by the end of the year, city officials said. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
