<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPER BALLOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am a new resident to Southern California, having moved here from New York in 
September, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 I am consistently amazed and delighted by the many forward looking 
advancements in this section of the country, not the least of which is the 
traffic control systems, road repair work, etc.It seems they start and finish 
many items in one day. And even the recent earthquake did not deter them from 
repair and reconstruction of the freeways. I applaud you greatly. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, will someone please enlighten me . How in this day and age do we still 
have paper ballots for major elections? I have been voting since 1947 in New 
York City. I have never used a paper ballot. I am sure they had election 
machines long before I started voting. 
</P>
<P>
 There must be a good reason. 
</P>
<P>
 JULIA H. RAHHAL 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Point 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
