<HEADLINE>
<P>
LADY MATADORS HEAD FOR TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge was not among the 48 teams selected Sunday to play in the 
NCAA Division I women's volleyball tournament, but the Matadors accepted an 
invitation to compete in the National Invitational Volleyball Championships in 
Kansas City starting Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge (17-8) will play Oregon State and Sam Houston State in pool play 
matches Friday, followed by contests against Connecticut and Minnesota on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners of the four five-team pools will meet in the semifinals Sunday 
morning, with the victors advancing to the championship match in the afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 This is the third time in five years that Northridge has been invited to the 
NIVC. The Matadors finished second to Houston in 1990 and tied for fifth in 
1991. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura College men's basketball team remained undefeated with a 93-55 
victory over Moorpark in the championship game of the Ventura tournament Sunday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Curtis Gaines led the Pirates (6-0) with 18 points and 11 rebounds. Lance Fay 
added 17 points. 
</P>
<P>
 For Moorpark (4-2), Paul Foster scored 13 points and Jim Harbour had 10. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game, Antelope Valley defeated Santa Barbara, 73-66. 
</P>
<P>
 The Marauders (4-4) were led by Orville Turner with 20 points. 
