Invitational at Hilo, Hawaii. The Boilermakers were trailing, 85-83, with 1:12 
to play in overtime when Martin made a three-point shot. Fred Hoiberg then 
scored with 32 seconds left to put the Cyclones ahead. . . . St. Louis made 
only one basket in the final 10:00, but made 14 of 17 free throws during that 
