<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; PERMIT FOR TRADE SCHOOL EXTENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council last week granted Jewelry Tech Institute an additional two 
years to operate a trade school at the Hoover Street Center. 
</P>
<P>
 School officials requested the longer permit to coincide with the five-year 
lease of two buildings at the business center, where the school is moving from 
its present location a block away on Garden Grove Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 In September, the Planning Commission granted the school, which offers courses 
in jewelry design and English to mostly Vietnamese students, a three-year 
permit. 
</P>
<P>
 Afy Harraf, the school's director of operations, said the school is 
transferring from its campus for the past 15 years at Western Avenue to the 
larger facilities at Hoover Street Center. The school has about 140 students, 
she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Harraf said the school likely would move in January. 
</P>
<P>
 The council last week also granted a request for a one-way entrance to the 
school from Garden Grove Boulevard and exits only onto Hoover Street. BERT 
ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
