<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LA HABRA; CARD DESIGNERS WIN MUSEUM MEMBERSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By NANCY HSU 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two elementary school students will be presented this week with one-year 
family memberships to the Children's Museum at La Habra and a box of Christmas 
cards they designed in a museum contest. 
</P>
<P>
 The designs of Danielle Morgan, a first-grader at Ladera Palma Elementary 
School, and Kristen Farrara, a student at Walnut School, were selected last 
month out of 300 entries.The contest, held in June, asked students to draw a 
Christmas scene, said Missy Fleet, president of Friends of the Children's 
Museum at La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
 Morgan's card features a Christmas tree with a yellow star ornament on top of 
it and a reindeer resembling "a stuffed bear with antlers" standing next to the 
tree, Fleet said. 
</P>
<P>
 Farrara's card features a snowman, complete with top hat and pipe. There are 
also snowflakes and a flower in the background, Fleet said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morgan and Farrara will get their prize, valued at $40, this Monday and 
Tuesday, respectively, at their schools. 
</P>
<P>
 A box of 12 cards is on sale at the museum's gift shop for $10. Funds raised 
from the card sales benefit the museum's programming fund. So far, the museum 
has sold more than 3,000 cards, Fleet said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Children's Museum at La Habra is at 301 S. Euclid St. NANCY HSU 
</P>
</TEXT>
