<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LAKE FOREST; TURN-OF-THE-CENTURY CHRISTMAS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County residents are invited to see what Christmas was like here at the 
turn of the century with a one-day Victorian Christmas celebration Saturday at 
Heritage Hill Historical Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The park, at 25151 Serrano Road, consists of an adobe house built by the 
Serrano family in 1863, and a one-room schoolhouse, a church and a farm house 
all built in the 1890s and early 1900s. 
</P>
<P>
 The grounds will be decorated with Victorian-era ornaments and lights. 
</P>
<P>
 Entertainment will include children's programs, dance troupes, carolers, and 
sales of holiday crafts. 
</P>
<P>
 This year's celebration is the 13th annual Christmas celebration presented by 
the Amigos de Colina, a volunteer group at the park. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration will run from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Admission is $3 for adults, 
and $2 for children ages 3 to 12. Information: (714) 855-2028.LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
