<P>
MARINE HELD IN CONNECTION WITH DEATH OF STEPSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Marine from Camp Pendleton was being held by military authorities in 
connection with the death of his 3-year-old stepson Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lance Cpl.Nathan Lewis, 20, of Albion, Mich., was placed in custody after 
questioning by the Naval Criminal Investigative Service, according to Cpl. Anne 
Donnelly, a base spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 The medical examiner's office in San Diego County has not determined a cause 
of death and an autopsy is scheduled for today, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday night, Camp Pendleton fire officials responded to an emergency 
call Lewis made from his residence on base and transported the child, Anthony 
Williamson, to the nearby Naval Hospital. Williamson was flown by Life Flight 
helicopter to Children's Hospital and Health Center in San Diego and died early 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 A 6-month-old boy, identified as Lewis' son Xavier, was also taken from the 
home to the Naval Hospital and was later transferred to the Naval Hospital's 
Child Protection Unit. 
</P>
