but I think we are considerably better." Keith, in his eighth season at Irvine, 
thinks the Vaqueros have a more talented team from top to bottom. His mission 
will be to find a lineup that can combine to do more than individual things 
well. "We've got guys who are good shooters and some who are good shot-blockers 
and some who are good rebounders, but we don't have too many guys who do a lot 
of things well," Keith said. "Those are the kinds of things we need to focus 
on, getting guys to play the whole game." Irvine will be smaller than in any of 
Keith's previous seasons, but he expects Carlson to provide interior defense 
and shot-blocking. Parker led the team in scoring over the summer, and joins 
Hill and Guinn as three-point threats. 
