nine guys we'll have on the varsity can shoot it," Orris said. "We're not a 
team that can pound it inside, so we're going to run and press a lot more to 
take advantage of our speed and athleticism." Fracalosy will be a chief scoring 
threat, with the ability to shoot the three and slash to the basket. DeGrazier, 
who split time between the varsity and junior varsity last year, and Owen will 
handle point-guard duties. While size might be lacking inside, Orris is pleased 
with the efforts of Schiff, Coleman, MacDonald and Klinke against bigger 
players. 
