<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL John Halagan: 24-28 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS 
YR. HGT. P Eric Ripley Sr. 6-3 F Todd Semm Sr. 6-3 F 04,15,05,06,04 TOP 
RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Ricky Jenkins Jr. 6-1 G 04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. 
HGT. P Mickey Brown Sr. 5-11 G Chris Burgess So. 6-9 C Brian Quinn Jr. 6-0 F 
William Stovall So. 6-0 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge became bigger and better instantly last spring when Burgess 
transferred from Mater Dei. Halagan, in his third year as Warriors coach, 
compares Burgess favorably with former Woodbridge standout Adam Keefe, now with 
the NBA's Utah Jazz. "Chris is a lot bigger than Adam was as a sophomore and 
even a little more versatile at this point, especially from the perimeter," 
Halagan said. "He's obviously going to be a very, very good player for us down 
the road." Halagan plans on using Burgess from a variety of positions on the 
floor, not just as a turn-and-shoot post player, to take advantage of Burgess' 
outside shooting touch. But it won't be all Burgess for Woodbridge. Semm and 
Ripley are third-year varsity players and Halagan expects them to increase 
their offensive output this season. The Warriors lack experience in the 
backcourt, but Halagan expects Jenkins, Brown and Stovall to progress quickly. 
Woodbridge could play as many as 10 or 11 players regularly in its trapping and 
pressing defensive style. 
