<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL BEGINS SEASON TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The high school boys' basketball season begins tonight with first-round games 
in the Buena Park, Pacific Shores and National Sports Grill Invitational 
tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
 Servite, one of the top teams in the Golden West League, and Pacifica, the 
defending champion in Southern Section Division III-A, are among those entered 
in the National Sports Grill Invitational at Loara and Savanna highs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Brea-Olinda, Mission Viejo and Daily Pilot Tip-Off Classic tournaments 
begin Tuesday. Katella, a preseason favorite to win the Empire League title, 
opens against Whittier Christian in the first round of the Brea-Olinda 
tournament Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley, which features one of the nation's top juniors, Olujimi 
Mann, opens with nonleague games on Wednesday at Sonora and on Friday against 
visiting Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei, which has won section titles in nine of the past 12 seasons, begins 
its season next week. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls' basketball season also begins tonight with five nonleague games 
scheduled. In a key nonleague game, Ocean View plays at Edison Tuesday before 
county tournaments begin on Wednesday. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
