<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: ARCO TRANSPORTATION NAMES HAZELWOOD A SENIOR VP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mark L. Hazelwood has been appointed senior vice president of pipeline 
operations for Long Beach-based Arco Transportation Co. Hazelwood, 45, will be 
responsible for Houston-based Arco Pipe Line Co. and Anchorage-based Arco 
Transportation Alaska Inc. Arco's pipeline operations involve transporting 
crude oil, refined petroleum products, and petrochemicals.Since February, 1994, 
Hazelwood has been senior vice president of ATC with management responsibility 
for Alaskan pipeline operations. Arco Transportation is a division of Atlantic 
Richfield Co., Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 * Patrick Courtin has been appointed chairman and chief executive of ComStream 
Inc. Courtin joined the San Diego-based firm's parent company, Spar Aerospace 
Ltd. of Mississauga, Ontario, in March as senior vice president, 
communications. He keeps that job in addition to his executive responsibilities 
at ComStream. He succeeds Ron Derry, who continues as ComStream president and 
chief operating officer, reporting to Courtin. ComStream provides 
satellite-based communications systems and networks for voice, data, imaging 
and video uses. 
</P>
<P>
 * Alethea Caldwell has joined Managed Health Network Inc. as president and 
chief operating officer. Before joining the Los Angeles-based managed 
behavioral health care and employee assistance company, Caldwell was executive 
vice president of Blue Cross of California. 
</P>
<P>
 * CytoProbe Corp. announced the appointment of M. Lee Hulsebus as chairman. 
Hulsebus, 55, will also retain his current positions as president and chief 
executive of the company. He succeeds B. Roland Freasier Jr., who remains a 
member of the board. The San Diego company develops, manufactures and markets 
specialty medical devices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
