<P>
 World Electric-Car Conference: The 12th International Electric Vehicle 
Symposium opens in Anaheim this week with an electric-car parade down 
Disneyland's Main Street on Thursday. Exhibits that include the first-ever 
views of some domestic and foreign vehicles will be open to the public Saturday 
and Sunday at the Disneyland Hotel and Convention Center. Monday through 
Wednesday of next week, electric-vehicle experts from around the world will 
discuss the latest technology and the challenge of delivering 
commercial-quality cars to the public.An international event since 1969, the 
EVS-12 symposiums -- in the shorthand of alternative-fuel vehicle promoters -- 
have been held in various U.S. cities, Germany, France, Canada, Hong Kong and 
elsewhere. The 1994 program was developed by the European Electric Road Vehicle 
Assn., the Electric Vehicle Assn. of the Asia-Pacific and the Electric Vehicle 
Assn. of the Americas. A long list of auto makers, environmentalists and 
air-quality regulators are lined up to speak during the conference sessions. 
For information about the public exhibits, call (714) 778-6600; about the 
symposium meetings: Pam Turner at (415) 855-8799. 
