<P>
 A Near-Smokeless Cigarette?: R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Co. has developed a 
near-smokeless cigarette that the company hopes tastes better than a similar 
product launched six years ago that flopped.The Eclipse produces little 
secondary smoke because it does not burn tobacco, although it does have as much 
nicotine as most cigarettes. Analysts said Eclipse could be a breakthrough 
product for RJR because it reduces secondary smoke and may help reduce 
incidence of cancer among smokers. However, RJR is keeping tight-lipped about 
the success of its marketing tests. 
