<TEXT>
<P>
 Employers Report Big Hiring Plans: According to the quarterly survey of 15,000 
businesses nationwide by the temporary employment agency Manpower Inc., 22% of 
those responding said they plan to add to their work forces in the first 
quarter of next year.That is fastest pace for a first quarter in six years. 
Twelve percent said they expect a drop, another 63% that they will remain at 
present levels, and 3% that they are unsure, the survey said. A year ago, 18% 
anticipated additional staffing and 13% planned decreases. Manufacturers have 
the most aggressive hiring plans; geographically, prospects continue to be 
strongest in the South and the Midwest. 
</P>
