</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dam Project Offering Set: The world's largest hydroelectric project, the Three 
Gorges Dam on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, will raise funds on the 
Hong Kong stock market, the official China Securities newspaper reported.The 
Three Gorges Dam Development Corp. will issue shares in its Gezhouba 
Hydroelectric Dam subsidiary, the paper said. That dam, also in the central 
province of Hubei, is completed and can pay dividends using its own electricity 
revenues. The money raised will be used to build the Three Gorges Dam, which 
will cost $13.3 billion, the paper said. 
