<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLINTON FAMILY ENDS 4-DAY CAMP DAVID STAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 President Clinton and his family returned to the White House on Sunday after a 
four-day stay at the snow-covered Camp David presidential retreat. 
</P>
<P>
 Wearing a brown sweater and matching jacket, Clinton bounded off Marine One 
with a smile, clapping his hands together once. Returning with the Clintons and 
their daughter, Chelsea, were his stepfather, Richard Kelley, and the First 
Lady's mother, Dorothy Rodham. 
</P>
<P>
 The White House said Clinton spent a quiet Thanksgiving weekend in the 
Catoctin Mountains in Maryland. 
</P>
