<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRIEST WANTED IN ASSAULT ARRESTED AT AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A priest wanted in the sexual assault of a 13-year-old New Jersey girl was 
arrested as he prepared to board a plane for Haiti. 
</P>
<P>
 Jean Level Eliscard, 28, was arrested Saturday at John F. Kennedy 
International Airport, officials said. He was charged with aggravated sexual 
contact and endangering the welfare of a child, according to police in Hamilton 
Township, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 Eliscard apparently realized he was a suspect and tried to leave the country, 
police allege. A tip from a member of his predominantly Haitian parish led 
police to the airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
